<topic id="dcpp_how_to_change_the_styling_of_the_page_numbering">
    <title>How to Change the Header Styling Depending on Page Side</title>
    <body>
        <p>In your <xref href="dcpp_the_customization_css.dita">customization css</xref> add the following CSS rule, to
            modify the styling of the default page headers:</p>
        <codeblock outputclass="language-css">@page :left {
    @top-left {
        color:navy;
        font-style:italic;
    }
    @top-right {
        color:red;
    }
}</codeblock>
        <p>If you intend to modify <b>just the headers of the table of contents</b>, use the
                <keyword>table-of-contents</keyword> page rule selector:</p>
        <codeblock outputclass="language-css">@page table-of-contents:left {
    @top-left {
        color:navy;
        font-style:italic;
    }
    @top-right {
        color:red;
    }
}</codeblock>
    </body>
